  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-af09e2440c66",
  "content": "# Write summary.json\n\n### Task 2: Dry-run the script and fix issues\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `scripts/benchmark.sh`\n\n**Step 1: Run preflight only (will fail at Phase 2+ without inference)**\n\nRun from repo root:\n```bash\ncd /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\n./scripts/benchmark.sh 2>&1 | head -20\n```\nExpected: \"Phase 1: Preflight\" passes, \"Binaries OK\" printed.\n\n**Step 2: Run full script**\n\nRun:\n```bash\n./scripts/benchmark.sh\n```\n\nWatch for:\n- corvia-inference starts and stays running\n- corvia.toml gets patched to provider=corvia\n- `corvia demo --keep` completes (ingest may take 1-2 minutes)\n- Server starts and /health responds\n- All 8 curl calls succeed (4 queries x 2 modes)\n- JSON files appear in benchmark-results/\n\n**Step 3: Fix any issues discovered during dry-run**\n\nCommon issues to watch for:\n- grpc health check might not respond to HTTP GET — may need to adjust `wait_for_grpc`\n- `corvia demo --keep` might need the working directory to be the repo root (for git adapter to find source files)\n- JSON response structure might differ from expected (field paths in jq)\n- sed patterns might not match exact corvia.toml format\n\n**Step 4: Verify output files**\n\nRun:\n```bash\ncat benchmark-results/*/summary.json | jq '.queries[].id'\n```\nExpected: `1 2 3 4`\n\n**Step 5: Commit fixes**\n\n```bash\ngit add scripts/benchmark.sh\ngit commit -m \"fix: benchmark script adjustments from dry-run\"\n```\n\n---\n\n\n### Task 3: Add benchmark-results to .gitignore\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `.gitignore`\n\n**Step 1: Check current .gitignore**\n\nRead: `.gitignore`\n\n**Step 2: Add benchmark-results directory**\n\nAppend:\n```",
